00:23:44,462 --> 00:23:45,982
even with metal detectors...

258
00:23:46,22 --> 00:23:48,302
even in this transit lounge.

259
00:23:49,862 --> 00:23:52,863
SIMON: Oh, it's so early.

260
00:23:52,903 --> 00:23:54,822
You guys wanna get coffee
or something?

261
00:23:56,762 --> 00:23:58,02
TRETIAK: Sure.

262
00:24:01,423 --> 00:24:03,303
Be quiet.

263
00:24:03,803 --> 00:24:06,82
SIMON: What is it
you request of my employer?

264
00:24:05,623 --> 00:24:07,983
TRETIAK: Do you know
what cold fusion is?

265
00:24:08,23 --> 00:24:09,423
SIMON: Of course.

266
00:24:09,963 --> 00:24:12,83
It's the theory...

267
00:24:11,624 --> 00:24:14,144
of nuclear fusion
at room temperature...

268
00:24:14,184 --> 00:24:15,264
free energy forever.

269
00:24:15,804 --> 00:24:17,45
TRETIAK: Yes.

270
00:24:17,84 --> 00:24:18,163
SERVER: Kaffee?

271
00:24:17,703 --> 00:24:18,783
SIMON: Klein, Bitte.

272
00:24:21,84 --> 00:24:24,765
SIMON: As far as science goes,
it ranks just above astrology.

273
00:24:24,265 --> 00:24:26,185
Those who claim to
have achieved the experiment...

274
00:24:26,224 --> 00:24:28,306
have never been able
to duplicate it.

275
00:24:28,845 --> 00:24:30,84
TRETIAK: Until now.

276
00:24:31,344 --> 00:24:35,265
There is an electrochemist
working at Oxford.

277
00:24:35,805 --> 00:24:38,86
We believe
that this good lady...

278
00:24:37,626 --> 00:24:40,426
made a breakthrough
in cold fusion.

279
00:24:40,466 --> 00:24:44,386
Your employer
will obtain the formula for me.

280
00:24:44,425 --> 00:24:48,66
He's very busy,
and you are very boring.

281
00:24:48,106 --> 00:24:49,866
Your offer must inspire him.

282
00:24:49,866 --> 00:24:52,386
This woman
has repeatedly avoided...

283
00:24:52,427 --> 00:24:56,106
my agents' attempts
to find the formula.

284
00:24:56,147 --> 00:24:58,147
She's cagey, difficult.

285
00:25:00,07 --> 00:25:02,208
Maybe your agents are stupid.

286
00:25:06,127 --> 00:25:10,48
I think this inspiration would
cost you three million dollars.

287
00:25:10,87 --> 00:25:12,288
TRETIAK: [Chuckles]
Ridiculous.

288
00:25:11,788 --> 00:25:16,388
SIMON: Why? You will have
the world market in energy.

289
00:25:16,429 --> 00:25:18,787
Cost you a nickel
for every million you make.

290
00:25:18,828 --> 00:25:20,68
His deposit should go--

291
00:25:20,108 --> 00:25:23,148
Hey. It is not for me.

292
00:25:23,189 --> 00:25:24,629
It is for mother Russia.

293
00:25:24,669 --> 00:25:28,430
But you want mother Russia,
too, Mr. Tretiak.

294
00:25:28,430 --> 00:25:32,69
Three million in a bank account
in Zurich. Agreed?

295
00:25:34,229 --> 00:25:35,789
Yes.

296
00:25:35,830 --> 00:25:40,909
How long to get
your employer's agreement?

297
00:25:40,950 --> 00:25:42,109
I'll ask.

298
00:25:56,911 --> 00:25:58,471
Your offer has inspired her.

299
00:25:59,11 --> 00:26:00,91
I'll do it.

300
00:26:01,231 --> 00:26:03,392
Bank account number in Zurich.

301
00:26:04,272 --> 00:26:06,152
Auf wiedersehen. Bye, sonny.

302
00:26:06,191 --> 00:26:07,912
TRETIAK: Bye-bye.

303
00:26:09,352 --> 00:26:13,473
I really love this guy.
Ha ha ha!

304
00:26:17,11 --> 00:26:19,12
ILYA:
Too bad we have to kill him.

305
00:26:19,52 --> 00:26:20,413
Yeah, too bad.

306
00:26:34,434 --> 00:26:37,154
WOMAN: When the electrochemists
Pons and Fleischman...

307
00:26:37,694 --> 00:26:40,94
announced in 1989...

308
00:26:39,634 --> 00:26:42,714
that they had discovered
cold fusion...

309
00:26:42,754 --> 00:26:46,875
a revolutionary process
of generating energy...

310
00:26:46,914 --> 00:26:50,275
they were at first
acclaimed as geniuses...

311
00:26:50,315 --> 00:26:53,34
and then condemned
as charlatans.

312
00:26:54,195 --> 00:26:57,75
The protocols of cold fusion...

313
00:26:57,116 --> 00:26:58,475
SIMON: What are those? Drugs?

314
00:26:59,16 --> 00:27:02,16
Could I have one?
My head's pounding.

315
00:27:02,55 --> 00:27:04,96
She's boring the life
out of me.

316
00:27:05,355 --> 00:27:07,356
-They're for my heart.
-Oh.

317
00:27:08,476 --> 00:27:11,637
You have very pretty eyes.
You're a pretty lady.

318
00:27:11,676 --> 00:27:14,37
-Who are you?
-Me?

319
00:27:14,37 --> 00:27:16,476
I'm here to do an interview
with that Dr. Russell.

320
00:27:17,17 --> 00:27:19,616
I'm gonna expose her as a fraud.

321
00:27:19,157 --> 00:27:21,997
You don't put any stock in
this cold fusion mumbo jumbo?

322
00:27:22,37 --> 00:27:24,78
-Actually, I do.
-Really?

323
00:27:24,117 --> 00:27:27,197
WOMAN: Dr. Emma Russell.

324
00:27:33,318 --> 00:27:35,238
Oops.

325
00:27:40,99 --> 00:27:45,499
EMMA: Well, I didn't prepare
any formal remarks.

326
00:27:45,39 --> 00:27:46,919
I'm actually more interested...

327
00:27:46,959 --> 00:27:50,319
in what questions you all have
about cold fusion...

328
00:27:50,360 --> 00:27:52,398
so I thought we would
start with those.

329
00:27:52,439 --> 00:27:54,439
Any questions?

330
00:27:56,639 --> 00:27:57,719
Please?

331
00:27:57,760 --> 00:27:59,200
MAN: I have, Dr. Russell.

332
00:28:00,200 --> 00:28:03,280
Can you explain
the actual process of fusion...

333
00:28:03,321 --> 00:28:04,880
you know, the theory?

334
00:28:04,919 --> 00:28:07,640
Yes. Oh, there it is.

335
00:28:08,181 --> 00:28:12,21
This is the--the apparatus.

336
00:28:12,61 --> 00:28:13,381
And very simply...

337
00:28:12,921 --> 00:28:16,40
when positively charged
deuterons...

338
00:28:16,81 --> 00:28:18,921
are attracted
to the palladium cathode...

339
00:28:18,961 --> 00:28:20,361
they cram together...

340
00:28:20,401 --> 00:28:23,801
and there are millions of them
inside the cathode...

341
00:28:23,842 --> 00:28:27,82
getting closer and closer,
and then they fuse...

342
00:28:27,122 --> 00:28:29,202
and they create energy
in the form of helium.

343
00:28:29,241 --> 00:28:30,762
WOMAN: But I read somewhere...

344
00:28:30,802 --> 00:28:32,482
that the experiment
couldn't be replicated...

345
00:28:33,22 --> 00:28:36,663
so how do we know it works?

346
00:28:36,203 --> 00:28:38,283
EMMA: We don't.

347
00:28:38,322 --> 00:28:39,442
Not yet.

348
00:28:41,23 --> 00:28:42,822
But if you remember Einstein...

349
00:28:42,362 --> 00:28:45,363
he knew the theory
of relativity to be true...

350
00:28:45,403 --> 00:28:47,164
long before he could prove it.

351
00:28:47,164 --> 00:28:47,724
I mean, he felt the truth.

352
00:28:47,724 --> 00:28:48,844
And, uh, some of us
feel the same way...

353
00:28:48,844 --> 00:28:52,363
And, uh, some of us
feel the same way...

354
00:28:52,904 --> 00:28:54,63
about cold fusion...

355
00:28:53,604 --> 00:28:55,963
because it's there.
It's in nature...

356
00:28:56,504 --> 00:29:01,64
the raw, natural power
just waiting to be harnessed.

357
00:29:00,605 --> 00:29:04,845
When we ignite
that cold fusion fire...

358
00:29:04,884 --> 00:29:07,84
I mean, just imagine.

359
00:29:08,165 --> 00:29:12,46
There's more energy
in one cubic mile of seawater...

360
00:29:12,85 --> 00:29:14,806
than in all the known
oil reserves on earth.

361
00:29:14,845 --> 00:29:18,765
I mean, you could drive
your car 55 million miles...

362
00:29:18,806 --> 00:29:21,165
on a gallon of heavy water.

363
00:29:21,206 --> 00:29:23,966
It would be the end
of pollution...

364
00:29:24,06 --> 00:29:26,447
warmth for the whole world.

365
00:29:27,925 --> 00:29:31,646
So why don't I demonstrate
for you...

366
00:29:31,687 --> 00:29:35,287
why other people in the past
have been so unsuccessful?

367
00:29:37,587 --> 00:29:39,27
They used very complex...

368
00:29:40,746 --> 00:29:43,27
SIMON: November 17, 11:30 a.m.

369
00:29:43,66 --> 00:29:45,587
Entering flat
of Dr. Emma Russell.

370
00:29:45,127 --> 00:29:46,328
High Street, Oxford.

371
00:29:47,328 --> 00:29:50,248
No alarms on outer doors.
Strange.

372
00:29:50,288 --> 00:29:51,847
TAPE: No messages.

373
00:29:57,48 --> 00:29:58,289
SIMON: Shelley Monument.

374
00:30:01,89 --> 00:30:02,369
Entering bathroom.

375
00:30:03,589 --> 00:30:05,29
Books.

376
00:30:06,888 --> 00:30:08,88
More books.

377
00:30:11,809 --> 00:30:14,410
Walls covered
with reminder notes.

378
00:30:16,949 --> 00:30:18,29
Poetry.

379
00:30:27,650 --> 00:30:28,770
[Click]

380
00:30:30,910 --> 00:30:33,71
Ah. Dad.

381
00:30:34,31 --> 00:30:35,791
[Click]

382
00:31:04,172 --> 00:31:06,333
"Stop and talk to Shelley
every day.

383
00:31:06,373 --> 00:31:08,853
"How can I love
a man named Percy?"

384
00:31:13,73 --> 00:31:14,993
"Isn't there
someone in the world...

385
00:31:15,33 --> 00:31:16,993
"who can consume me like that."

386
00:31:17,34 --> 00:31:20,154
Magic. Romantic.

387
00:31:27,994 --> 00:31:29,35
No recent applications.

388
00:31:29,115 --> 00:31:31,35
"Cold fusion notes."

389
00:31:41,496 --> 00:31:43,616
"Although I pass the
Shelley Monument every day...

390
00:31:43,616 --> 00:31:45,896
"its sadness strikes me
every time."

391
00:31:47,216 --> 00:31:50,256
"l feel a very personal loss
when I look at it.

392
00:31:50,295 --> 00:31:52,256
"So much pain
and so much passion."

393
00:31:57,497 --> 00:31:59,977
"To give light to them
that sit in darkness...

394
00:32:00,17 --> 00:32:01,458
"and in the shadow of death."

395
00:32:03,296 --> 00:32:05,857
"Luke 1; verse 79."

396
00:32:05,897 --> 00:32:08,778
Tretiak's wrong.
She's not cagey.

397
00:32:09,898 --> 00:32:12,738
She's not difficult.
She's just...

398
00:32:12,778 --> 00:32:14,18
eccentric.

399
00:32:14,698 --> 00:32:16,658
She's innocent.

400
00:32:22,979 --> 00:32:24,99
Maybe it's in her head.

401
00:32:26,79 --> 00:32:29,758
She needs a poet...
an artist...

402
00:32:30,779 --> 00:32:32,619
someone who...

403
00:32:32,660 --> 00:32:35,340
understands truth.

404
00:32:43,80 --> 00:32:44,841
She needs Thomas More.

405
00:33:13,62 --> 00:33:14,262
[Taps paper]

406
00:33:29,384 --> 00:33:30,663
SIMON: Do you like it?

407
00:33:32,824 --> 00:33:33,824
EMMA: What?

408
00:33:33,864 --> 00:33:36,943
The sculpture. Do you like it?

409
00:33:38,344 --> 00:33:41,744
Oh...yes.

410
00:33:41,784 --> 00:33:43,624
What do you love about it?

411
00:33:52,985 --> 00:33:58,66
The way it...glows.

412
00:33:58,746 --> 00:34:01,865
And how the light...

413
00:34:01,906 --> 00:34:04,426
holds him in silence...

414
00:34:05,465 --> 00:34:07,466
taking care of him.

415
00:34:09,607 --> 00:34:12,86
That's what I like about it.

416
00:34:15,146 --> 00:34:16,466
Are you an artist?

417
00:34:17,07 --> 00:34:22,327
No. I'm just a traveler
searching for purity.

418
00:34:22,748 --> 00:34:25,426
-What do you search for?
-Energy.

419
00:34:25,467 --> 00:34:27,308
Yes.

420
00:34:29,868 --> 00:34:32,708
Have you ever been
on a long journey?

421
00:34:32,747 --> 00:34:34,468
No, not really.

422
00:34:37,188 --> 00:34:39,749
Perhaps I'll take you
to my home...

423
00:34:39,788 --> 00:34:41,908
in Africa.

424
00:34:41,949 --> 00:34:44,429
You should
experience the energy...

425
00:34:44,469 --> 00:34:46,190
of where all life began.

426
00:34:51,789 --> 00:34:54,790
Sorry.
I'm not very good with people.

427
00:34:58,750 --> 00:35:00,470
Me, neither.

428
00:35:28,132 --> 00:35:31,52
EMMA: "l see my angel
for the first time...

429
00:35:31,92 --> 00:35:34,92
"know my purpose,
feel my birth..."

430
00:35:35,73 --> 00:35:38,272
"hear, at first faintly,
then distinctly...

431
00:35:38,312 --> 00:35:40,672
"the sweet strains
of our union..."

432
00:35:41,873 --> 00:35:45,273
"Our love heats up
the cold universe...

433
00:35:45,314 --> 00:35:48,33
"and gives my tired,
desperate hope..."

434
00:35:48,73 --> 00:35:50,833
SIMON: "purified
by our kisses...

435
00:35:51,374 --> 00:35:54,53
"are eternally healed."

436
00:35:55,154 --> 00:35:56,435
Do you like it?

437
00:35:56,435 --> 00:35:58,674
Who did you write it for?

438
00:35:58,714 --> 00:36:01,114
SIMON: You.

439
00:36:01,654 --> 00:36:05,54
You're following me,
or it's destiny.

440
00:36:05,94 --> 00:36:07,535
Either way, it's weird.

441
00:36:07,575 --> 00:36:09,55
Very weird.

442
00:36:11,535 --> 00:36:13,15
Destiny then.

443
00:36:22,956 --> 00:36:24,716
This must look strange.

444
00:36:26,895 --> 00:36:28,96
It's, uh...

445
00:36:28,136 --> 00:36:31,97
something that I'm working on...

446
00:36:30,636 --> 00:36:32,276
a formula for...

447
00:36:33,276 --> 00:36:35,397
creating energy.

448
00:36:35,996 --> 00:36:38,37
That you carry around
in your underwear?

449
00:36:39,677 --> 00:36:42,877
Yeah, I do.

450
00:36:55,278 --> 00:36:57,79
How did you do that?

451
00:36:58,999 --> 00:37:01,78
Magic.

452
00:37:01,119 --> 00:37:02,798
EMMA: Give it back.

453
00:37:02,838 --> 00:37:04,319
SIMON: It looks like Sanskrit.

454
00:37:04,358 --> 00:37:06,238
Give it back.

455
00:37:09,99 --> 00:37:11,939
I'm sorry. I just wanted
to watch you put it away.

456
00:37:14,99 --> 00:37:16,219
What else do you keep in there?

457
00:37:17,20 --> 00:37:18,100
Nothing.

458
00:37:17,640 --> 00:37:18,999
SIMON: That's not true.

459
00:37:20,641 --> 00:37:23,319
SERVER: Can I get you
anything else?

460
00:37:25,759 --> 00:37:29,800
SIMON: Drink your wine.
Latour '57.

461
00:37:31,401 --> 00:37:34,801
WAITER: The Latour, sir,
is $400 a bottle.

462
00:37:38,881 --> 00:37:41,01
Then we'll have two bottles.

463
00:37:44,162 --> 00:37:45,882
There. You count it.

464
00:37:51,843 --> 00:37:55,243
SIMON: All these little tubes
and microbes and things.

465
00:37:55,282 --> 00:37:56,603
EMMA: Molecules?

466
00:37:56,643 --> 00:37:58,683
-Those, too.
-[Laughs]

467
00:37:58,724 --> 00:38:01,282
EMMA: Can I tell you something?

468
00:38:01,322 --> 00:38:03,282
SIMON:
What? You must. Everything.

469
00:38:03,323 --> 00:38:05,763
EMMA: [Whispering]
It's a secret.

470
00:38:05,804 --> 00:38:06,924
SIMON: What?

471
00:38:08,804 --> 00:38:10,284
I'm done.

472
00:38:12,843 --> 00:38:15,964
My energy research--
I'm finished.

473
00:38:16,04 --> 00:38:19,284
I still have some sequencing
that I have to work out...

474
00:38:19,324 --> 00:38:22,405
to make sure that it's safe,
but I did it.

475
00:38:23,604 --> 00:38:27,44
It's just been you against
the whole world, hasn't it?

476
00:38:27,85 --> 00:38:29,645
How have you done it
and stayed so positive?

477
00:38:29,684 --> 00:38:31,325
The gift of faith.

478
00:38:33,86 --> 00:38:35,285
To see...

479
00:38:36,645 --> 00:38:37,965
Well...

480
00:38:38,06 --> 00:38:41,486
to believe in something
that's all around us...

481
00:38:42,486 --> 00:38:45,486
but hidden from our sight.

482
00:38:46,207 --> 00:38:47,966
SIMON:
That's a beautiful thought.

483
00:38:48,05 --> 00:38:50,06
EMMA: I can't believe
I'm telling you this.

484
00:38:51,606 --> 00:38:54,87
I don't even know your name.

485
00:38:54,126 --> 00:38:55,607
Well, my name is...

486
00:38:57,247 --> 00:38:58,686
I don't want to tell you.

487
00:38:58,727 --> 00:39:00,766
I don't want to do that.

488
00:39:02,607 --> 00:39:05,207
I don't want to do that.
What difference does it make?

489
00:39:07,488 --> 00:39:08,608
What's your name?

490
00:39:09,849 --> 00:39:12,48
-Emma.
-Emma.

491
00:39:12,87 --> 00:39:14,727
Now I know
everything about you.

492
00:39:16,508 --> 00:39:19,28
Your...genius.

493
00:39:20,489 --> 00:39:22,208
You have a weak heart.

494
00:39:25,769 --> 00:39:29,649
You have beautiful dreams,
great courage.

495
00:39:30,729 --> 00:39:33,210
You're not afraid in this world.

496
00:39:33,250 --> 00:39:35,129
You get that from your father.

497
00:39:37,370 --> 00:39:39,809
You can't cook
to save your life...

498
00:39:40,970 --> 00:39:42,251
and you love fish.

499
00:39:44,651 --> 00:39:46,210
I do love fish.

500
00:39:47,249 --> 00:39:49,410
That's weird.

501
00:39:49,451 --> 00:39:51,11
I want to try that.

502
00:39:51,550 --> 00:39:53,70
-No.
-Yes.

503
00:39:53,111 --> 00:39:55,31
I don't want you to.
Drink your wine.

504
00:39:56,931 --> 00:39:58,91
EMMA: Yes, I do.

505
00:39:59,371 --> 00:40:00,651
What's your name?

506
00:40:02,671 --> 00:40:05,71
My name is Thomas More.

507
00:40:04,612 --> 00:40:08,93
I was named after the saint...

508
00:40:10,72 --> 00:40:13,312
who died for his faith.

509
00:40:14,612 --> 00:40:15,733
OK.

510
00:40:18,173 --> 00:40:19,333
Your work...

511
00:40:20,773 --> 00:40:23,813
is very dangerous...
and alive...

512
00:40:25,453 --> 00:40:27,133
and I love your poems.

513
00:40:27,893 --> 00:40:29,254
They move me.

514
00:40:30,973 --> 00:40:32,774
But that's not
who you really are.

515
00:40:34,693 --> 00:40:36,93
You're running away from...

516
00:40:37,134 --> 00:40:39,735
your past and your pain...

517
00:40:40,334 --> 00:40:43,895
and yet you keep it
so close to you.

518
00:40:46,414 --> 00:40:50,95
So you don't have to be afraid
of who you are...

519
00:40:52,175 --> 00:40:54,16
because you're beautiful.

520
00:41:50,459 --> 00:41:51,740
What are you doing?

521
00:42:09,201 --> 00:42:14,41
EMMA: Oh, my God,
you're bleeding. What happened?

522
00:42:14,81 --> 00:42:16,241
SIMON: Don't know. I was...

