00:43:20,665 --> 00:43:22,186
I mean, your sweater.

547
00:43:26,126 --> 00:43:29,07
EMMA: There's blood on it.
I'll wash it.

548
00:43:33,306 --> 00:43:34,626
SIMON: Very domestic.

549
00:43:35,947 --> 00:43:39,707
There's blood
on your blouse as well.

550
00:43:42,448 --> 00:43:44,07
I'll wash it.

551
00:43:57,348 --> 00:43:58,828
Do you have any wine?

552
00:44:10,109 --> 00:44:15,670
EMMA: I'm so overwhelmed
that you even noticed me.

553
00:44:15,709 --> 00:44:17,150
SIMON: How could I not?

554
00:44:19,710 --> 00:44:21,349
You make me feel so good.

555
00:44:21,889 --> 00:44:23,10
I wish you...

556
00:44:24,430 --> 00:44:26,30
I wish you could understand.

557
00:44:28,371 --> 00:44:31,91
I want you to know who I am.

558
00:44:46,952 --> 00:44:48,152
Oh, my heart.

559
00:44:49,691 --> 00:44:52,52
Don't disappear.
I'll be right back.

560
00:44:52,92 --> 00:44:54,812
FEMALE VOCALIST:
Calm it down.

561
00:44:55,33 --> 00:44:56,872
Bring it round.

562
00:44:56,912 --> 00:45:00,752
Too way high up, your street.

563
00:45:02,433 --> 00:45:05,353
I can see...

564
00:45:05,394 --> 00:45:07,873
like nothin' else...

565
00:45:07,913 --> 00:45:11,313
in me, you're better
than I wanna be.

566
00:45:14,54 --> 00:45:17,215
Don't think,
'cause I understand...

567
00:45:16,715 --> 00:45:18,74
Don't think,
'cause I understand...

568
00:45:18,114 --> 00:45:19,833
I care...

569
00:45:19,874 --> 00:45:22,274
Don't think,
'cause I'm talking...

570
00:45:22,314 --> 00:45:24,915
SIMON: Oh, I can't do this.

571
00:45:24,954 --> 00:45:26,154
She's so great.

572
00:45:26,695 --> 00:45:28,55
EMMA: I can't believe this.

573
00:45:28,94 --> 00:45:30,536
I can't believe
this is happening.

574
00:45:30,796 --> 00:45:33,675
VOCALIST: I'm open...

575
00:45:34,175 --> 00:45:37,56
to falling from grace.

576
00:45:49,57 --> 00:45:50,976
[Song continues faintly]

577
00:45:55,676 --> 00:45:56,877
EMMA: Hi.

578
00:46:13,158 --> 00:46:15,38
ILYA: "To spider:

579
00:46:15,118 --> 00:46:17,719
"Must fly. Have better offer."

580
00:46:18,479 --> 00:46:20,878
Greedy westerner.
Wants more money.

581
00:46:20,918 --> 00:46:22,118
TRETIAK: Who cares?

582
00:46:22,159 --> 00:46:25,39
Can't spend hard currency
in hell.

583
00:46:27,79 --> 00:46:28,759
Send this message--

584
00:46:28,799 --> 00:46:31,999
"Fly, don't buzz off.

585
00:46:33,359 --> 00:46:35,439
"I'll double your fee...

586
00:46:36,759 --> 00:46:41,00
"or send my own boys
to take care of the woman."

587
00:46:48,361 --> 00:46:50,280
EMMA: You OK?

588
00:46:52,81 --> 00:46:56,801
SIMON: Let's...
let's just lie here.

589
00:46:58,881 --> 00:47:01,481
Can't we just
be like this tonight?

590
00:47:03,322 --> 00:47:05,363
Is that what you want?

591
00:47:06,42 --> 00:47:07,801
SIMON: It's so magic.

592
00:47:13,602 --> 00:47:15,362
It just feels so perfect.

593
00:47:18,762 --> 00:47:19,763
[Beeping]

594
00:47:45,44 --> 00:47:47,605
RADIO: It's 7:00 a.m.,
and here are the news headlines.

595
00:47:56,325 --> 00:47:57,726
EMMA: Thomas?

596
00:49:11,291 --> 00:49:13,811
TRETIAK: Lev Naumovitch,
it's here! Good man!

597
00:49:13,850 --> 00:49:15,292
DR. BOTVIN:
It's revolutionary, sir!

598
00:49:15,292 --> 00:49:18,251
She's boldly cast aside
a slew of stale ideas...

599
00:49:18,291 --> 00:49:20,732
but I think the formula
is incomplete.

600
00:49:20,771 --> 00:49:21,851
It will take months...

601
00:49:21,891 --> 00:49:23,91
TRETIAK: That won't do...

602
00:49:23,132 --> 00:49:26,12
because now that the people are
nicely beginning to freeze...

603
00:49:26,52 --> 00:49:29,612
Tretiak must sweep in
with a miracle to save them.

604
00:49:29,651 --> 00:49:31,892
MAN: How high do you want it,
Mr. Tretiak?

605
00:49:31,932 --> 00:49:34,292
TRETIAK: To the top.
Good morning, Yuri.

606
00:49:34,832 --> 00:49:36,73
YURI: Good morning.

607
00:49:36,112 --> 00:49:39,33
BOTVIN: Perhaps l
can confirm the validity...

608
00:49:39,73 --> 00:49:41,673
of this formula more quickly
if I dispense...

609
00:49:41,213 --> 00:49:44,52
with certain protocols.
But, Mr. Tretiak--

610
00:49:44,93 --> 00:49:46,173
YURI: How long, Dr. Botvin,
since you received...

611
00:49:46,213 --> 00:49:49,894
your last salary check
from Moscow University?

612
00:49:49,933 --> 00:49:52,774
BOTVIN:
Ukrainian Independence Day.

613
00:49:54,373 --> 00:49:55,493
Last August.

614
00:49:56,34 --> 00:49:58,434
[Beeping]

615
00:49:57,974 --> 00:50:00,174
Ivan, he's on-line.

616
00:50:02,174 --> 00:50:03,254
TRETIAK: Do it.

617
00:50:06,494 --> 00:50:07,655
SIMON: To spider...

618
00:50:09,935 --> 00:50:11,495
You've got the recipe.

619
00:50:12,35 --> 00:50:13,235
YURI: "Where's my dough?"

620
00:50:12,776 --> 00:50:14,776
TRETIAK: To human fly...

621
00:50:16,15 --> 00:50:19,216
Recipe incomplete.

622
00:50:19,255 --> 00:50:21,176
The cake won't rise.

623
00:50:21,215 --> 00:50:24,95
Hence, no dough.

624
00:50:30,256 --> 00:50:32,496
SIMON: I am not the baker...

625
00:50:33,37 --> 00:50:35,557
YURI: "...but don't make me
the butcher."

626
00:50:37,257 --> 00:50:38,977
I like this guy.

627
00:50:42,976 --> 00:50:45,897
No play, no pay.

628
00:50:45,938 --> 00:50:49,418
I'm certain you kept
the cookbook.

629
00:50:57,698 --> 00:50:58,778
ILYA: Holland Park.

630
00:51:13,739 --> 00:51:15,420
RECEPTIONIST:
I'll check that for you.

631
00:51:15,460 --> 00:51:18,460
Yes, that seems to be fine.
One moment. Aah!

632
00:51:27,381 --> 00:51:29,21
SIMON: He's keeping me on-line.

633
00:51:38,461 --> 00:51:39,701
MAN: You wait here.

634
00:51:55,362 --> 00:51:58,03
[Sirens]

635
00:52:05,143 --> 00:52:06,983
[Beeping]

636
00:52:06,983 --> 00:52:08,103
[Beeping]

637
00:52:21,264 --> 00:52:23,905
POLICE OFFICER:
You, beside the car.

638
00:52:24,985 --> 00:52:28,664
Now, turn around.
Step away from the vehicle.

639
00:52:28,705 --> 00:52:29,825
SIMON: He's armed!

640
00:52:52,346 --> 00:52:53,467
ILYA: Drive!

641
00:53:02,707 --> 00:53:05,67
ILYA: Go the other way. Go!

642
00:53:09,787 --> 00:53:11,987
MALE VOCALIST:
You're all I've got tonight.

643
00:53:13,388 --> 00:53:15,868
You're all I've got tonight.

644
00:53:18,28 --> 00:53:19,309
INSPECTOR: What about him?

645
00:53:27,629 --> 00:53:29,149
What about this one?

646
00:53:33,669 --> 00:53:35,950
EMMA: Yeah. That--

647
00:53:35,989 --> 00:53:39,150
INSPECTOR: We believe
they're all the same villain.

648
00:53:43,750 --> 00:53:45,150
Oh, my God.

649
00:53:47,110 --> 00:53:49,231
They're all him?

650
00:53:49,271 --> 00:53:50,911
INSPECTOR: We believe so.

651
00:53:50,952 --> 00:53:53,791
He eluded a hit squad
this morning in Holland Park.

652
00:53:55,991 --> 00:53:58,391
Then he fled the U.K.
out of Heathrow.

653
00:53:58,431 --> 00:54:00,152
WOMAN: We've got a handful
of false identities...

654
00:54:00,691 --> 00:54:04,51
used on visas,
passports, leases...

655
00:54:04,751 --> 00:54:05,991
Nicholas Owen...

656
00:54:05,991 --> 00:54:08,112
Louie Guanella...

657
00:54:08,151 --> 00:54:09,312
Peter Damian...

658
00:54:10,712 --> 00:54:12,873
Charles Borroneo.

659
00:54:12,913 --> 00:54:15,352
EMMA: Of course.

660
00:54:15,392 --> 00:54:18,72
Thomas More.

661
00:54:18,113 --> 00:54:20,113
All names of Catholic saints.

662
00:54:23,473 --> 00:54:25,874
Can you access
Heathrow's passenger lists...

663
00:54:25,913 --> 00:54:28,873
for the last eight hours?

664
00:54:29,473 --> 00:54:31,73
I think it might be possible.

665
00:54:31,114 --> 00:54:32,233
Good.

666
00:54:36,615 --> 00:54:38,55
[Bell rings]

667
00:54:38,94 --> 00:54:39,613
[Crowd cheering]

668
00:54:40,74 --> 00:54:41,194
ILYA: Go!

669
00:54:58,995 --> 00:55:00,75
CROWD: Yeah!

670
00:55:05,916 --> 00:55:07,476
[Singing in Russian]

671
00:55:11,357 --> 00:55:12,477
MAN: Yes!

672
00:55:23,798 --> 00:55:25,238
TRETIAK: See, my friends...

673
00:55:25,958 --> 00:55:28,918
you back the biggest rats.

674
00:55:31,277 --> 00:55:33,198
[Speaking Russian]

675
00:55:49,240 --> 00:55:50,359
Hello.

676
00:55:54,239 --> 00:55:55,719
TRETIAK: Out, out.

677
00:55:55,799 --> 00:55:58,160
Freeloaders, out.

678
00:55:58,160 --> 00:55:59,760
I want to drink alone.

679
00:55:59,800 --> 00:56:01,40
Close the curtain.

680
00:56:22,641 --> 00:56:24,362
-What?
-What?

681
00:56:26,761 --> 00:56:28,722
SIMON: Don't look down.

682
00:56:28,761 --> 00:56:30,602
You know who I am?

683
00:56:31,762 --> 00:56:32,882
No.

684
00:56:33,422 --> 00:56:37,22
I'm the thief
you tried to cheat.

685
00:56:37,63 --> 00:56:39,903
This is your accountant.

686
00:56:41,642 --> 00:56:43,83
Talk to him.

687
00:56:45,724 --> 00:56:48,164
SIMON: The phone goes
the other way, you moron.

688
00:56:51,683 --> 00:56:53,244
Hello.

689
00:56:53,283 --> 00:56:54,884
Tretiak speaking.

690
00:56:55,723 --> 00:57:00,125
That money to Zurich,
send it now.

691
00:57:00,164 --> 00:57:01,645
I said now.

692
00:57:03,84 --> 00:57:04,324
Yeah.

693
00:57:06,844 --> 00:57:07,965
Thank you.

694
00:57:08,965 --> 00:57:12,686
You know what the hardest part
about being you is?

695
00:57:12,725 --> 00:57:15,244
Pretending to be so bad in bed.

696
00:57:17,126 --> 00:57:19,326
You son of the bitch.

697
00:57:20,45 --> 00:57:22,406
SIMON: There is an impostor.
Get him out.

698
00:57:22,446 --> 00:57:24,926
TRETIAK: Hey, hey, hey!

699
00:57:25,466 --> 00:57:29,26
Take your hands off me,
you idiots!

700
00:57:29,65 --> 00:57:31,346
Are you crazy? It's me.

701
00:57:30,887 --> 00:57:32,06
Go, go!

702
00:57:32,46 --> 00:57:33,366
Catch him, go!

703
00:57:33,366 --> 00:57:35,247
Ilya, get the bastard!

704
00:57:42,367 --> 00:57:44,288
[Siren]

705
00:57:48,08 --> 00:57:49,607
[Radio dispatcher
speaking Russian]

706
00:57:57,169 --> 00:57:59,449
SIMON: Fifty million. I'm out.

707
00:58:01,928 --> 00:58:03,849
SIMON: Mr. Ferrer checking out.

708
00:58:03,888 --> 00:58:06,408
CLERK: OK.
[Speaking Russian]

709
00:58:10,969 --> 00:58:12,890
[Speaking Russian]

710
00:58:15,889 --> 00:58:18,289
EMMA: I'll have one, too.

711
00:58:18,890 --> 00:58:19,970
SIMON: Emma.

712
00:58:20,10 --> 00:58:21,850
EMMA: Hi.

713
00:58:22,811 --> 00:58:25,410
I'm...I'm overwhelmed.

714
00:58:27,170 --> 00:58:28,251
You found me.

715
00:58:28,290 --> 00:58:29,891
Wasn't very hard.

716
00:58:31,131 --> 00:58:34,731
Two men with saint's names
flew into Moscow yesterday.

717
00:58:34,771 --> 00:58:38,690
Isadore Bakanja
is a short, bald African...

718
00:58:38,731 --> 00:58:41,132
whereas Vincent Ferrer--

719
00:58:41,171 --> 00:58:43,212
SIMON: Named after a saint
who betrayed his best friend.

720
00:58:43,251 --> 00:58:45,131
How could you do it?

721
00:58:45,612 --> 00:58:47,492
Emma...

722
00:58:48,32 --> 00:58:50,631
l--l had to.

723
00:58:51,451 --> 00:58:52,652
I'm a thief.

724
00:58:52,692 --> 00:58:54,612
I want my cards back.

725
00:58:55,153 --> 00:58:57,72
SIMON: You flew all this way
for your cards?

726
00:58:56,613 --> 00:58:57,692
Yes, I did.

727
00:58:57,733 --> 00:59:00,293
No.
It's because you're in love.

728
00:59:03,933 --> 00:59:05,173
I rest my case.

729
00:59:05,212 --> 00:59:06,974
Who are you?

730
00:59:07,13 --> 00:59:10,54
No one has a clue,
least of all me.

731
00:59:10,93 --> 00:59:13,734
EMMA: And why would you
steal cold fusion?

732
00:59:13,773 --> 00:59:16,973
It's free.
Why would you do that?

733
00:59:17,14 --> 00:59:19,14
[Bartender speaking Russian]

734
00:59:19,54 --> 00:59:20,694
Eight million reasons.

735
00:59:20,735 --> 00:59:23,335
Eight million.
Wow. That's all?

736
00:59:25,14 --> 00:59:28,375
I would have
given them to you...

737
00:59:28,414 --> 00:59:30,215
if you'd only asked.

738
00:59:36,376 --> 00:59:37,695
You've got
to get away from me.

739
00:59:37,736 --> 00:59:41,56
I'm not going until you tell me
why you lied to me.

740
00:59:41,595 --> 00:59:44,76
-You lied to me.
-l lied to you?

741
00:59:43,615 --> 00:59:46,56
You almost got me killed.
The guy says it doesn't work.

742
00:59:46,96 --> 00:59:47,817
Well, screw him.

743
00:59:47,856 --> 00:59:50,56
I don't think you'd enjoy that.

744
00:59:50,96 --> 00:59:51,976
EMMA: You're right.
I don't think I would.

745
00:59:54,56 --> 00:59:55,457
[Speaking Russian]

746
00:59:59,338 --> 01:00:02,337
Emma, you don't know
what you're dealing with here.

747
01:00:03,937 --> 01:00:05,338
EMMA: What?

748
01:00:13,738 --> 01:00:15,378
-They took my pills.
-No, they didn't.

749
01:00:15,418 --> 01:00:17,418
I palmed them from your purse.

750
01:00:17,959 --> 01:00:20,78
I need one or two.

751
01:00:19,619 --> 01:00:22,659
I need...
I have a bad heart.

752
01:00:22,699 --> 01:00:25,378
-I know.
-It's starting to pound.

753
01:00:25,378 --> 01:00:26,859
SIMON:
It's OK. I've got your pills.

754
01:00:26,859 --> 01:00:27,979
OK, I've got two in my hand.

755
01:00:27,979 --> 01:00:30,699
OK, I've got two in my hand.

756
01:00:30,699 --> 01:00:31,899
EMMA: I'm gonna pass out.

757
01:00:31,939 --> 01:00:33,740
Sit down on the floor.

758
01:00:35,300 --> 01:00:38,379
Just get down on the floor.
That's right.

759
01:00:38,420 --> 01:00:40,180
That's right.
Eat two out of my hand.

760
01:00:40,219 --> 01:00:43,621
That's right. OK?

761
01:00:43,660 --> 01:00:46,21
While you're down there...

762
01:00:49,160 --> 01:00:51,40
Get the pocketknife
out of my boot.

763
01:00:53,100 --> 01:00:56,781
This formula makes
certain assumptions...

764
01:00:56,822 --> 01:01:01,21
which contradict all we know
about cold fusion cathodes...

765
01:01:01,60 --> 01:01:03,221
so testing at any level
becomes futile...

766
01:01:03,262 --> 01:01:06,822
without further information,
Mr. Tretiak.

767
01:01:07,362 --> 01:01:10,42
TRETIAK:
Don't despair, Dr. Botvin.

768
01:01:10,83 --> 01:01:11,482
Help is here.

769
01:01:22,144 --> 01:01:23,862
The two came very quietly.

770
01:01:26,142 --> 01:01:27,303
Oh.

771
01:01:32,344 --> 01:01:35,25
TRETIAK:
And they left even more quietly.

772
01:01:36,703 --> 01:01:38,64
Close the city.

773
01:01:39,04 --> 01:01:43,605
Kill him, and bring her...alive.

774
01:01:43,644 --> 01:01:45,45
[Sirens]

775
01:01:57,246 --> 01:02:00,05
Why are they after me?

776
01:02:00,46 --> 01:02:04,165
Tretiak, the guy I work for...
he owns this city, cops and all.

777
01:02:03,706 --> 01:02:07,826
We have to convince him there's
nothing more he wants from you.

778
01:02:07,826 --> 01:02:09,866
EMMA: What do you want from me?

779
01:02:15,747 --> 01:02:19,147
-Everything's on those cards?
-Yes.

780
01:02:19,188 --> 01:02:20,628
SIMON: So the formula works?

781
01:02:20,667 --> 01:02:23,148
Oh, kiss me again.

782
01:02:25,427 --> 01:02:26,867
-No.
-Make up your mind.

783
01:02:26,867 --> 01:02:31,908
Oh, it's--l have to
figure out the order...

784
01:02:31,949 --> 01:02:34,628
before the formula works,
and I'm not giving it to him.

785
01:02:34,668 --> 01:02:36,668
-Tretiak will find you.
-No.

786
01:02:36,708 --> 01:02:39,108
He found me,
and that's hard to do.

787
01:02:39,149 --> 01:02:43,109
-l found you.
-Yes, you did.

788
01:02:43,149 --> 01:02:44,429
What do you need?

789
01:02:48,828 --> 01:02:50,710
I need some time...

790
01:02:50,749 --> 01:02:51,989
and I need...

791
01:02:54,230 --> 01:02:57,70
I need a place to work...

792
01:02:57,110 --> 01:02:58,671
and...

793
01:02:59,670 --> 01:03:01,829
EMMA:
Where's everyone going?

794
01:03:01,870 --> 01:03:05,111
SIMON: To their country
relatives to cut firewood.

795
01:03:05,150 --> 01:03:06,791
There's no heat in the city.

796
01:03:08,671 --> 01:03:10,990
[Dialing telephone]

797
01:03:11,30 --> 01:03:12,431
[Loud rock music playing]

798
01:03:17,91 --> 01:03:19,131
How long will it take you
to finish the formula?

799
01:03:18,672 --> 01:03:20,231
I don't know.

800
01:03:20,272 --> 01:03:23,351
Two hours, maybe.
I don't know.

801
01:03:23,391 --> 01:03:25,952
Should be enough time to get
our passports together...

802
01:03:25,992 --> 01:03:28,832
and for us to get married.

803
01:03:28,871 --> 01:03:31,472
-We're getting married?
-Yes.

804
01:03:33,92 --> 01:03:36,251
I want you to be
Mrs. Martin de Porres.

805
01:03:39,432 --> 01:03:41,833
-You're not Martin.
-No.

806
01:03:43,273 --> 01:03:44,433
Who are you?

807
01:03:47,793 --> 01:03:49,193
I don't have a name.

808
01:03:50,753 --> 01:03:51,954
That's sad.

809
01:03:51,993 --> 01:03:54,274
Will you have a name
when we get home?

810
01:03:54,314 --> 01:03:56,154
I don't have a home.

811
01:03:56,194 --> 01:03:57,874
When we get back...

812
01:03:57,915 --> 01:04:00,114
you do the science,
I'll do the math.

813
01:04:00,154 --> 01:04:01,835
We'll market your formula
around the world.

814
01:04:02,395 --> 01:04:04,995
We'll make a fortune,
and then...

815
01:04:06,635 --> 01:04:07,795
we'll see.

816
01:04:09,156 --> 01:04:10,795
OK?

817
01:04:19,35 --> 01:04:20,316
Emma!

818
01:04:22,76 --> 01:04:23,955
[Horn honking]

819
01:04:38,96 --> 01:04:39,657
MAN: No trouble, OK?

820
01:04:43,58 --> 01:04:46,258
If you want to live,
never leave my side.

821
01:05:31,921 --> 01:05:33,81
Ohh!

822
01:05:36,321 --> 01:05:37,600
[Splash]

823
01:06:41,646 --> 01:06:42,967
[Music blaring]
Spice room, sun room...

824
01:06:43,06 --> 01:06:45,47
Shadow room, night...

825
01:06:46,446 --> 01:06:48,166
EMMA: I've got you.

826
01:06:54,406 --> 01:06:55,927
EMMA: Come on.

827
01:07:00,87 --> 01:07:01,927
Here we go. Up.

828
01:07:05,287 --> 01:07:07,848
We've gotta get you warm.

829
01:07:16,28 --> 01:07:17,788
We're almost there.

830
01:07:40,910 --> 01:07:42,70
EMMA: Come on.

831
01:07:42,890 --> 01:07:44,770
Come on.

832
01:07:49,930 --> 01:07:52,971
You'll wait till Christ
comes to Moscow.

833
01:07:53,11 --> 01:07:55,612
Elevator was made of mahogany.

834
01:07:55,651 --> 01:07:57,731
Tenants used it
for firewood last winter.

835
01:07:57,770 --> 01:07:59,291
EMMA: We need your help.

836
01:07:59,331 --> 01:08:02,11
He fell in the river,
and he's freezing.

837
01:08:02,52 --> 01:08:03,692
-Need clothes.
-We're just people--

838
01:08:03,732 --> 01:08:08,12
You're not people.
You're Americans.

839
01:08:08,53 --> 01:08:11,172
Yes, but we ran into trouble
with your Mafia.

840
01:08:11,212 --> 01:08:12,291
[Tires screech]

841
01:08:32,934 --> 01:08:34,53
[Speaking Russian]

842
01:08:34,53 --> 01:08:35,733
[Speaking Russian]

843
01:08:42,15 --> 01:08:46,414
She disapproves of what I do,
but eats the bread it buys her.

844
01:08:48,335 --> 01:08:50,455
No heat for sale...

845
01:08:50,495 --> 01:08:52,336
but these clothes
will make him warm.

846
01:08:52,375 --> 01:08:55,736
[Speaking Russian]

847
01:08:58,76 --> 01:09:00,596
I tell her, Mashenka,
go back to bed.

848
01:09:00,135 --> 01:09:02,135
She's always puttering around.

849
01:09:05,777 --> 01:09:09,616
It's here.
Built to escape Secret Police.

850
01:09:09,656 --> 01:09:11,97
In you go.

851
01:09:25,178 --> 01:09:27,498
EMMA: You've got hypothermia.

852
01:09:28,37 --> 01:09:30,438
We have to get
these wet clothes off...

853
01:09:31,299 --> 01:09:32,378
keep you warm.

854
01:09:33,217 --> 01:09:35,378
ILYA: They must be in
one of these buildings.

855
01:09:35,417 --> 01:09:37,18
Check every apartment.

856
01:09:38,898 --> 01:09:41,939
EMMA:
How you doing? Talk to me.

857
01:09:41,979 --> 01:09:44,699
SIMON: Snug as a bug in a rug.

858
01:09:52,419 --> 01:09:55,740
OK. We're gonna...

859
01:09:55,779 --> 01:09:59,660
We're gonna have to do this
before your body temperature...

860
01:10:00,200 --> 01:10:03,40
falls below 95 degrees.

861
01:10:14,821 --> 01:10:17,662
MAN: Two kids
talking about foreigners.

862
01:10:23,941 --> 01:10:26,182
[Bell rings]

863
01:10:26,222 --> 01:10:27,862
ILYA: Listen to me, tenants!

864
01:10:28,702 --> 01:10:30,863
Show me where
the Americans are...

865
01:10:30,902 --> 01:10:34,742
and you'll be paid
in American dollars.

866
01:10:34,783 --> 01:10:37,63
Five hundred bucks reward.

867
01:10:37,63 --> 01:10:38,263
Daddy...

868
01:10:39,784 --> 01:10:42,864
have you seen, by chance,
two Americans?

869
01:10:43,403 --> 01:10:46,83
Just one American
and one polar bear.

870
01:10:45,623 --> 01:10:47,383
[Woman laughs]

871
01:10:47,424 --> 01:10:49,223
Do we get 250?

872
01:10:58,43 --> 01:11:00,284
[Woman speaking Russian]

873
01:11:08,184 --> 01:11:09,304
ILYA: We check upstairs.

874
01:11:10,465 --> 01:11:11,624
[Door closes]

875
01:11:21,225 --> 01:11:22,666
EMMA: What's your name?

876
01:11:25,946 --> 01:11:27,347
Who are you really?

877
01:11:29,306 --> 01:11:30,427
Simon.

878
01:11:30,467 --> 01:11:31,666
Simon?

879
01:11:33,87 --> 01:11:36,47
So you are named for a saint.

880
01:11:36,87 --> 01:11:37,847
No, Simon the magician.

881
01:11:38,227 --> 01:11:40,267
I did tricks...

882
01:11:40,307 --> 01:11:43,747
tricks for Agnes...
and that's how I got things.

883
01:11:43,787 --> 01:11:47,627
Priests took everything,
took Agnes.

884
01:11:47,668 --> 01:11:49,668
Dogs too big.

885
01:11:49,708 --> 01:11:52,669
Teeth. Teeth.

886
01:11:52,708 --> 01:11:54,429
She fell.

887
01:11:54,468 --> 01:11:55,787
I escaped.

888
01:11:57,188 --> 01:11:58,308
I always escape.

889
01:11:59,628 --> 01:12:02,28
I don't believe in magic
anymore.

890
01:12:03,629 --> 01:12:04,909
EMMA: I do.

891
01:12:07,468 --> 01:12:10,69
I've never felt
like this before.

892
01:12:11,229 --> 01:12:12,349
How?

893
01:12:13,710 --> 01:12:15,190
I'm freezing.

894
01:12:19,630 --> 01:12:21,309
WOMAN: These are here!

895
01:12:28,151 --> 01:12:30,951
EMMA: We gotta get out of here.
Are you OK?

896
01:12:30,990 --> 01:12:33,71
They're coming.

897
01:12:34,31 --> 01:12:36,632
WOMAN: Americans are here!

898
01:12:36,671 --> 01:12:38,991
EMMA:
Hurry. Here, put this on.

899
01:12:45,92 --> 01:12:46,212
MAN: Ilya!

900
01:12:51,12 --> 01:12:52,492
[Siren]

901
01:12:58,793 --> 01:13:00,33
Upstairs. Go!

902
01:13:17,354 --> 01:13:18,874
EMMA: Maybe we can jump.

903
01:13:19,954 --> 01:13:21,434
Let's jump.

904
01:13:25,395 --> 01:13:27,155
Come on.

905
01:13:51,797 --> 01:13:52,957
Wait.

906
01:14:10,57 --> 01:14:11,538
We need her alive, idiot.

907
01:14:14,18 --> 01:14:15,659
SIMON: Embassy's east of here.

908
01:14:23,959 --> 01:14:25,359
[Arguing in Russian]

909
01:14:34,219 --> 01:14:36,19
WOMAN: You're late.
Where have you been?

910
01:14:36,279 --> 01:14:37,919
I've been waiting two hours.

911
01:14:37,960 --> 01:14:41,480
I've got some beautiful
paintings for you to buy.

912
01:14:42,19 --> 01:14:43,500
In here. Come on.

913
01:14:47,800 --> 01:14:50,961
Don't fret.
It's just my curator, Toli.

914
01:14:51,00 --> 01:14:53,600
I am Alexa Frankievitch,
but being you're Americans...

915
01:14:53,641 --> 01:14:55,441
you can call me Frankie.

916
01:14:55,480 --> 01:14:57,481
SIMON: OK, Frankie.
I've got money. We want--

917
01:14:58,21 --> 01:15:01,861
FRANKIE: I know. The icon
of the Virgin of the Damned.

918
01:15:01,402 --> 01:15:03,762
-Are those maps of the tunnels?
-Yes.

919
01:15:03,802 --> 01:15:06,481
We're not here to buy art.
Take us to the American Embassy.

920
01:15:07,22 --> 01:15:09,982
FRANKIE: Right.
I need $10,000 up-front.

921
01:15:10,22 --> 01:15:12,302
SIMON: No.

922
01:15:11,802 --> 01:15:15,202
OK. 7,000 and not a penny less.

923
01:15:15,243 --> 01:15:16,642
TOLI: Shh.

924
01:15:23,923 --> 01:15:25,363
[Whispering] Police.

925
01:15:25,404 --> 01:15:27,364
SIMON: No. Tretiak's goons.

926
01:15:36,124 --> 01:15:37,285
FRANKIE: Wait.

927
01:15:37,324 --> 01:15:40,204
ILYA: Sasha,
go east to the embassy.

928
01:15:40,245 --> 01:15:42,163
-Are we lost?
-What's wrong?

929
01:15:42,204 --> 01:15:45,404
FRANKIE: You're in Russia, sir.
Everything is complicated.

930
01:15:45,404 --> 01:15:46,485
But you know the way?

931
01:15:46,604 --> 01:15:50,46
Like the face
of a Bulgari chronograph.

932
01:15:59,925 --> 01:16:01,766
I remember. This way.

933
01:16:05,966 --> 01:16:08,606
FRANKIE: At last. Water main.

934
01:16:09,866 --> 01:16:12,67
They shut it down
each afternoon in winter.

935
01:16:11,606 --> 01:16:13,167
SIMON: What time do they
turn it back on?

936
01:16:13,207 --> 01:16:16,487
FRANKIE: You have five minutes,
plus or minus.

937
01:16:17,27 --> 01:16:18,106
EMMA: Plus or minus?

938
01:16:17,647 --> 01:16:20,06
TOLI: That means several
minutes earlier or later.

939
01:16:20,06 --> 01:16:23,47
FRANKIE: Don't worry.
Third opening is your embassy.

940
01:16:40,489 --> 01:16:42,328
Quick. Someone's coming.

941
01:16:47,889 --> 01:16:50,370
Come on. Come on.

942
01:16:57,849 --> 01:16:59,810
SIMON: Here's the second one.

943
01:17:00,351 --> 01:17:02,70
Embassy's next.

944
01:17:05,130 --> 01:17:08,650
-About two more minutes.
-Yeah. Unless it's minus.

945
01:17:12,331 --> 01:17:14,932
SIMON: Damn.
It's sealed.

946
01:17:16,410 --> 01:17:18,131
We'll have to go back.

947
01:17:18,171 --> 01:17:19,331
EMMA: Come on.

948
01:17:34,52 --> 01:17:36,13
[Distant rumbling]

949
01:17:42,833 --> 01:17:44,33
Hurry.

950
01:17:53,214 --> 01:17:55,174
SIMON: Up you go.

951
01:18:13,936 --> 01:18:16,854
MAN: Yankee, go home!
Down with Yankee!

952
01:18:16,895 --> 01:18:18,736
[Crowd chanting in Russian]

953
01:18:24,876 --> 01:18:28,36
Embassy's only
about 100 yards away.

954
01:18:28,77 --> 01:18:31,516
There's a car right above us.
Watch your head.

955
01:18:34,416 --> 01:18:35,936
[Hissing]

956
01:18:38,177 --> 01:18:40,97
[Crowd chanting in Russian]

957
01:19:03,20 --> 01:19:04,938
SIMON: I'll create a diversion.

958
01:19:04,979 --> 01:19:07,659
It should take you 10 seconds
to run to those gates.

959
01:19:08,199 --> 01:19:10,79
They'll open them
when they see you coming.

960
01:19:10,460 --> 01:19:12,139
EMMA: OK. I can do that.

961
01:19:12,180 --> 01:19:14,220
You can do it.

962
01:19:14,260 --> 01:19:18,100
Wait. When am I gonna see you?

963
01:19:18,139 --> 01:19:20,60
I'll find you. You found me.

964
01:19:20,100 --> 01:19:21,700
Yeah, I did.

965
01:19:50,782 --> 01:19:51,902
Aah!

966
01:20:21,985 --> 01:20:25,345
EMMA: I'm an American!
Open the gate!

967
01:20:25,385 --> 01:20:27,824
Open the gate!
I'm an American!

968
01:20:29,04 --> 01:20:31,125
MARINE: Back off from the gate.

969
01:20:31,165 --> 01:20:34,05
Back off. I said back off.

970
01:20:35,85 --> 01:20:38,366
Stand back from the gate.

971
01:20:40,05 --> 01:20:41,445
I said back off!

972
01:20:53,427 --> 01:20:54,867
SIMON: She outran you?

973
01:20:54,906 --> 01:20:56,867
How humiliating.

974
01:21:01,87 --> 01:21:04,207
One...shot left.

975
01:21:05,308 --> 01:21:07,268
Can't come
all the way to Russia...

976
01:21:07,307 --> 01:21:09,988
and not play Russian roulette.

977
01:21:10,28 --> 01:21:12,189
Before you shoot me,
want to know where the money is?

978
01:21:12,228 --> 01:21:13,788
[Clicks]

979
01:21:13,829 --> 01:21:15,427
Whose money?

980
01:21:15,468 --> 01:21:17,28
Tretiak's, yours.

981
01:21:17,67 --> 01:21:19,428
He treats you like dirt.
You could have it all.

982
01:21:19,468 --> 01:21:20,949
ILYA: What are you saying?

983
01:21:20,988 --> 01:21:23,109
I'm saying your father
stashed billions...

984
01:21:23,149 --> 01:21:26,30
and I know where it's hidden.
Let's make a deal.

985
01:21:26,569 --> 01:21:30,89
So...where are all those
hidden billions?

986
01:21:30,309 --> 01:21:34,69
I know...but I don't think
I'm gonna tell you.

987
01:21:56,871 --> 01:21:59,232
[Sirens]

988
01:22:02,670 --> 01:22:05,432
MAN: Joseph, what's the holdup?
I said get 'em inside!

989
01:22:05,471 --> 01:22:07,351
DOCTOR: You're worse
than all the others.

990
01:22:07,392 --> 01:22:09,993
However, burns will heal.

991
01:22:10,532 --> 01:22:13,92
Maybe a little chance
of scarring, perhaps...

992
01:22:12,633 --> 01:22:15,873
but all in all,
I'd say he's a very lucky boy.

993
01:22:15,873 --> 01:22:18,152
ILYA: Lucky? Look at me.

994
01:22:19,532 --> 01:22:22,93
I am a damn devil.

995
01:22:21,633 --> 01:22:23,113
TRETIAK: Christ.

996
01:22:26,273 --> 01:22:27,353
Yes?

997
01:22:27,393 --> 01:22:30,394
BOTVIN: I have run every test
on this cold fusion formula...

998
01:22:30,433 --> 01:22:34,794
and must conclude
it is not merely incomplete...

999
01:22:34,834 --> 01:22:37,34
but rather...impossible.

1000
01:22:37,75 --> 01:22:40,714
You may as well try to create
perpetual motion.

1001
01:22:41,635 --> 01:22:44,355
I invest millions...

1002
01:22:46,14 --> 01:22:48,855
and you can't make it work!

1003
01:22:51,634 --> 01:22:54,435
What are you doing
with my money?

1004
01:22:56,995 --> 01:23:00,676
Do you think it comes so easy?

1005
01:23:00,717 --> 01:23:01,835
No!

1006
01:23:01,875 --> 01:23:03,835
BOTVIN: But, sir...

1007
01:23:03,876 --> 01:23:08,357
I have been working for
nearly two weeks without sleep.

1008
01:23:08,396 --> 01:23:12,797
At first blush, the theorem
appears quite convincing.

1009
01:23:12,837 --> 01:23:14,316
It does?

1010
01:23:19,96 --> 01:23:23,217
Yes. It does.

1011
01:23:23,438 --> 01:23:24,718
Good man.

1012
01:23:24,758 --> 01:23:27,317
We can use it
to destroy our enemies.

1013
01:23:29,37 --> 01:23:32,398
TRETIAK: Only Dr. Russell
can spoil my plan.

1014
01:23:32,438 --> 01:23:35,119
If she gets back to London
and speaks to the press...

1015
01:23:35,158 --> 01:23:38,838
YURI: From here to the airport
are three army checkpoints...

1016
01:23:38,878 --> 01:23:40,678
all of them loyal to us.

1017
01:23:40,718 --> 01:23:42,719
TRETIAK: Make certain
they get the message--

1018
01:23:43,259 --> 01:23:46,19
she doesn't leave Moscow alive.

1019
01:23:47,960 --> 01:23:49,160
Mr. President.

1020
01:23:49,200 --> 01:23:52,200
As former Vice-minister
of Energy and Power...

1021
01:23:52,239 --> 01:23:57,319
I hear all manner of schemes
that provide cheaper energy.

1022
01:23:57,360 --> 01:24:00,800
And as our countrymen
freeze to death...

1023
01:24:00,841 --> 01:24:04,160
I've become aware of
a marvelous new technology...

1024
01:24:04,201 --> 01:24:07,41
about which I'm hopelessly
out of my league...

1025
01:24:07,80 --> 01:24:09,721
from a scientific viewpoint.

1026
01:24:09,761 --> 01:24:12,881
That's why I brought
our eminent physicist here...

1027
01:24:12,921 --> 01:24:16,41
Dr. Lev Botvin from
the University of Moscow.

1028
01:24:16,580 --> 01:24:19,61
AIDE: Before we are dazzled
by the good news...

1029
01:24:18,602 --> 01:24:21,162
let's dispense with the bad.

1030
01:24:21,201 --> 01:24:23,322
What is the price
of this marvel?

1031
01:24:23,362 --> 01:24:26,81
YURI: The cost of research
and development are there...

1032
01:24:26,121 --> 01:24:29,682
which is all
you are asked to defray.

1033
01:24:35,63 --> 01:24:37,702
Ten billion in hard currency?

1034
01:24:37,242 --> 01:24:42,163
I can't even pay my teachers,
my miners, my doctors.

1035
01:24:49,364 --> 01:24:51,283
Where are you heading?

1036
01:24:51,324 --> 01:24:54,604
I thought we'd drink
some vodka to get warmer.

1037
01:24:58,645 --> 01:25:01,604
Like the miracle of socialism...

1038
01:25:01,644 --> 01:25:04,844
our miracle
of cold fusion failed.

1039
01:25:04,885 --> 01:25:06,04
But no matter.

1040
01:25:06,44 --> 01:25:10,165
We have sold cold fusion
to President Karpov.

1041
01:25:10,206 --> 01:25:13,605
We will use the scandal
of its failure to destroy him.

1042
01:25:13,645 --> 01:25:16,405
The army must be mobilized
by midnight tomorrow.

1043
01:25:16,445 --> 01:25:19,926
You're a man in a hurry.
That's only one day.

1044
01:25:19,966 --> 01:25:23,246
ILYA: Not now, old witch.
We're working.

1045
01:25:23,287 --> 01:25:24,685
TRETIAK: Yes. Think of it.

1046
01:25:24,726 --> 01:25:30,326
One day, you can be proud again
to be a Russian general...

1047
01:25:30,366 --> 01:25:34,327
with a big nuclear missile
where your prick used to be.

1048
01:25:34,367 --> 01:25:37,367
AIDE: You must complete a form
before you get on a flight home.

1049
01:25:37,407 --> 01:25:38,966
Any medical problems?

1050
01:25:39,07 --> 01:25:40,447
EMMA: I have a heart condition.

1051
01:25:40,487 --> 01:25:42,928
AIDE: Do you need me to arrange
any medication for you?

1052
01:25:43,808 --> 01:25:46,248
EMMA: Well, I haven't
needed a pill.

1053
01:25:46,768 --> 01:25:47,928
That's strange.

1054
01:25:47,968 --> 01:25:50,07
MARINE: Get a form from
table three down the corridor.

1055
01:25:50,48 --> 01:25:51,488
I'll be back in 10 minutes...

1056
01:25:52,27 --> 01:25:54,148
by your side,
all the way to the airport.

1057
01:25:53,688 --> 01:25:54,808
EMMA: Thank you.

1058
01:25:54,848 --> 01:25:57,09
REPORTER: ...Across the street
in central Moscow...

1059
01:25:57,49 --> 01:26:01,489
where a mob attacked several
companies with ties to America.

1060
01:26:02,28 --> 01:26:05,829
Apparently, four U.S. citizens
were injured in the attack.

1061
01:26:05,409 --> 01:26:07,169
I'm told
that all American citizens...

1062
01:26:07,209 --> 01:26:09,729
have been asked to report
to the American embassy...

1063
01:26:09,770 --> 01:26:11,609
for immediate evacuation.

1064
01:26:11,650 --> 01:26:14,809
MAN: [Southern accent]
Excuse me. You look lost.

1065
01:26:14,849 --> 01:26:17,249
-No, I'm fine.
-May I help you?

1066
01:26:17,249 --> 01:26:21,810
Allow me to introduce myself.
My name is August Christopher.

1067
01:26:21,850 --> 01:26:25,290
Named after Saint Augustine,
who coined my favorite phrase--

1068
01:26:25,330 --> 01:26:27,771
"Give me chastity
and give me constancy...

1069
01:26:27,810 --> 01:26:30,331
"but do not give it yet."

1070
01:26:32,931 --> 01:26:34,251
[Protesters chanting in Russian]

1071
01:26:34,291 --> 01:26:37,691
Simon, I'm on the next flight
out of here.

1072
01:26:37,731 --> 01:26:38,892
Are you coming with me?

1073
01:26:38,931 --> 01:26:42,292
No. But they are.

1074
01:26:48,211 --> 01:26:51,692
I'll need you to develop
a sudden fear of flying.

1075
01:26:52,232 --> 01:26:54,33
Find a quiet room.

1076
01:26:54,372 --> 01:26:56,613
Finish the formula
and fax it back to me.

1077
01:26:56,652 --> 01:26:58,333
My number's on the back.

1078
01:26:58,373 --> 01:27:02,13
I don't understand.
Why are you keeping my cards?

1079
01:27:02,53 --> 01:27:03,813
I've got to deal
with the Russians...

1080
01:27:03,852 --> 01:27:05,854
or you'll never be safe.

1081
01:27:06,393 --> 01:27:08,74
Be good at school.

1082
01:27:07,614 --> 01:27:08,733
Wait.

1083
01:27:11,94 --> 01:27:14,14
-Don't you trust me, darlin'?
-Trust who?

1084
01:27:15,353 --> 01:27:17,34
SIMON: That hurts, Emma.

1085
01:27:17,74 --> 01:27:19,634
EMMA: I'm serious.
What's your name?

1086
01:27:19,174 --> 01:27:21,854
My name is August Christopher.

1087
01:27:21,895 --> 01:27:24,774
Of course I trust you,
August Christopher.

1088
01:27:24,815 --> 01:27:26,734
I mean, Vincent Ferrer...

1089
01:27:26,775 --> 01:27:28,895
I mean, Martin de Porres...

1090
01:27:30,95 --> 01:27:31,855
Thomas More.

1091
01:27:32,975 --> 01:27:35,814
After all,
you are my personal saint.

1092
01:27:37,235 --> 01:27:39,76
You have to be a very good...

1093
01:27:38,615 --> 01:27:42,16
and, usually, a very dead person
to become a saint.

1094
01:27:42,556 --> 01:27:46,37
And more importantly,
you have to work three miracles.

1095
01:27:46,77 --> 01:27:48,276
Now, get to work.

1096
01:27:49,36 --> 01:27:50,636
Who's that man?

1097
01:27:50,176 --> 01:27:52,457
AIDE: You're leaving
on the transport at 9:00, ma'am?

1098
01:27:52,496 --> 01:27:55,377
Probably be your
last chance out of here.

1099
01:27:55,417 --> 01:27:56,857
Better hurry. It's leaving.

1100
01:27:59,137 --> 01:28:01,657
YURI: Your troops
will depose the president...

1101
01:28:02,197 --> 01:28:05,38
and install Ivan Tretiak
as leader of Russia.

1102
01:28:05,77 --> 01:28:09,638
TRETIAK: Moscow must be
ringed with tanks by evening.

1103
01:28:09,178 --> 01:28:12,378
Don't worry.
The people will follow me.

1104
01:28:12,918 --> 01:28:15,78
They will be crying
for revolution.

1105
01:28:14,618 --> 01:28:17,98
YURI: Still, no one's
guessed the simple truth...

1106
01:28:17,138 --> 01:28:19,139
of where the heating oil went.

1107
01:28:19,179 --> 01:28:20,859
[Laughter]

1108
01:28:23,179 --> 01:28:25,858
TRETIAK: Who would believe
that a sea of oil...

1109
01:28:25,899 --> 01:28:28,459
was hidden under
this very building?

1110
01:28:28,499 --> 01:28:30,60
[Laughter]

1111
01:28:30,99 --> 01:28:32,940
Yuri, I understand
your Nataly is to...

1112
01:28:32,979 --> 01:28:35,459
WOMAN: Francis, you devil...

1113
01:28:36,00 --> 01:28:38,239
I heard you came here,
and you didn't call me.

1114
01:28:37,779 --> 01:28:41,20
-Hello, Dominic--
-Give me a ring, Charles.

1115
01:28:41,59 --> 01:28:43,660
MAN: Lou,
I've heard on the grapevine...

1116
01:28:43,701 --> 01:28:46,900
you're brokering a revolutionary
new energy source.

1117
01:28:47,740 --> 01:28:49,941
If it's as good
as it's cracked up to be...

1118
01:28:49,980 --> 01:28:53,101
I have friends who can double
your best offer...

1119
01:28:53,141 --> 01:28:55,221
on deposit in Zurich...

1120
01:28:55,262 --> 01:28:58,22
within one hour
of delivery and confirmation.

1121
01:28:58,820 --> 01:28:59,941
I'll be waiting.

1122
01:29:11,342 --> 01:29:12,461
[Door opens]

1123
01:29:20,383 --> 01:29:22,104
The work could be here.

1124
01:29:22,143 --> 01:29:23,983
This machine could work,
couldn't it?

1125
01:29:24,22 --> 01:29:26,623
[Guards shouting in Russian]

1126
01:29:26,664 --> 01:29:28,263
Who are you?

1127
01:29:28,304 --> 01:29:30,343
SIMON:
A friend of Dr. Russell's.

1128
01:29:30,884 --> 01:29:32,44
BOTVIN: Dr. Russell?

1129
01:29:33,624 --> 01:29:35,624
What's this equation?

1130
01:29:35,663 --> 01:29:36,984
It's so simple.

1131
01:29:38,384 --> 01:29:40,464
This is the key
to Dr. Russell's formula.

1132
01:29:41,04 --> 01:29:42,284
Yes.

1133
01:29:42,325 --> 01:29:44,05
[Guards speaking Russian]

1134
01:29:44,44 --> 01:29:46,205
The alarm. You had better go.

1135
01:29:45,745 --> 01:29:49,625
I need a miracle.
You've got 12 hours.

1136
01:29:51,105 --> 01:29:53,186
But Mr. Tretiak's rally
is tonight.

1137
01:29:53,225 --> 01:29:54,826
Can you make it work?

1138
01:29:56,925 --> 01:29:58,46
Make it work.

1139
01:30:01,906 --> 01:30:03,305
GUARD: What is wrong here?

1140
01:30:03,346 --> 01:30:04,706
BOTVIN: Uh, the alarm...

1141
01:30:07,306 --> 01:30:09,147
Uh...uh...

1142
01:30:09,867 --> 01:30:11,266
I tripped.

1143
01:30:19,747 --> 01:30:23,146
[Russian accent]
You are Nikolai Petrovich.

1144
01:30:23,187 --> 01:30:24,827
You are Nikolai Provovich--

1145
01:30:24,867 --> 01:30:26,28
Petrovich.

1146
01:30:28,147 --> 01:30:29,267
[Doorbell buzzes]

1147
01:30:36,668 --> 01:30:38,628
Tunnel built by KGB...

1148
01:30:40,789 --> 01:30:43,69
Leads to machine room
in Kremlin.

1149
01:30:43,109 --> 01:30:47,148
SIMON: Do you know where
the president's quarters are?

1150
01:30:47,189 --> 01:30:50,990
FRANKIE:
President Karpov is there.

1151
01:30:51,29 --> 01:30:55,30
But there are many guards,
so I suggest--

1152
01:30:55,70 --> 01:30:56,991
An alternate route?

1153
01:30:57,30 --> 01:30:59,830
Money. Now.

1154
01:31:01,710 --> 01:31:03,230
SIMON: Oh, ye of little faith.

1155
01:31:05,831 --> 01:31:08,430
NEWSWOMAN:
Russia stands tonight...

1156
01:31:08,471 --> 01:31:11,191
on the brink
of a second revolution.

1157
01:31:11,230 --> 01:31:13,670
As the number of deaths
from freezing mounts...

1158
01:31:14,211 --> 01:31:16,91
hundreds of thousands
of protesters...

1159
01:31:15,631 --> 01:31:17,712
have taken to the streets.

1160
01:31:17,752 --> 01:31:19,311
Even as
Russian President Karpov...

1161
01:31:19,852 --> 01:31:22,12
is promising
a mysterious solution...

1162
01:31:22,52 --> 01:31:23,892
to the crippling
heating-oil shortage...

1163
01:31:23,931 --> 01:31:26,51
troops opposed
to the elected government...

1164
01:31:26,92 --> 01:31:28,332
and led
by General Leo Sklarov...

1165
01:31:28,332 --> 01:31:31,13
have begun to ring
the Russian capital city.

1166
01:31:31,52 --> 01:31:32,932
Angry, frightened citizens...

1167
01:31:32,473 --> 01:31:35,152
are gathering outside
the Kremlin in Red Square...

1168
01:31:35,192 --> 01:31:36,952
but they're not braving
the bitter cold...

1169
01:31:36,952 --> 01:31:38,993
for yet another political rally.

1170
01:31:39,33 --> 01:31:42,353
They've been drawn here by
the promise of a revelation...

1171
01:31:42,393 --> 01:31:43,753
whatever that may be...

1172
01:31:43,794 --> 01:31:46,193
in what's become
a life-and-death struggle...

1173
01:31:46,233 --> 01:31:49,113
for the future
of democracy in Russia.

1174
01:31:58,713 --> 01:32:00,154
[Protesters shouting
in Russian]

1175
01:32:19,796 --> 01:32:20,956
[Door shuts]

1176
01:33:01,438 --> 01:33:04,159
SIMON: Mr. President?
I'm your friend.

1177
01:33:04,159 --> 01:33:05,919
KARPOV: What do you want?

1178
01:33:07,720 --> 01:33:10,879
I want to help you
to destroy Tretiak.

1179
01:33:10,919 --> 01:33:12,639
I need you to listen
for about 30 seconds.

1180
01:33:14,399 --> 01:33:17,80
I'm all right. Stay outside.

1181
01:33:17,120 --> 01:33:19,41
Please, continue.

1182
01:33:19,80 --> 01:33:22,400
Tonight you'll stand trial
in Red Square before the world.

1183
01:33:22,400 --> 01:33:25,640
Whatever Tretiak accuses you of,
I need you to admit to it.

1184
01:33:25,681 --> 01:33:27,160
Agree with this criminal?

1185
01:33:27,201 --> 01:33:29,961
If you want
to destroy Tretiak...yes.

1186
01:33:46,942 --> 01:33:49,61
Gruschev,
take Mr. Karpov downstairs.

1187
01:33:48,602 --> 01:33:49,762
The wife stays here.

1188
01:33:49,762 --> 01:33:51,842
[Mrs. Karpov speaking Russian]

1189
01:33:51,883 --> 01:33:55,163
Get your hands off!
What you are doing is illegal!

1190
01:33:55,203 --> 01:33:57,82
The people won't stand for it!

1191
01:33:57,122 --> 01:34:00,442
The people are too cold
to stop it. Who are you?

1192
01:34:14,124 --> 01:34:16,804
CROWD: Tretiak!
Tretiak! Tretiak!

1193
01:34:21,324 --> 01:34:23,244
[Crowd cheering]

1194
01:34:32,66 --> 01:34:34,105
Friends...

1195
01:34:33,645 --> 01:34:35,485
countrymen...

1196
01:34:36,25 --> 01:34:38,106
Russians!

1197
01:34:46,886 --> 01:34:51,46
You heard about this morning's
sensational events.

1198
01:34:51,86 --> 01:34:54,87
Many shocking documents
were recovered...

1199
01:34:54,127 --> 01:34:56,286
from the president's
secret files...

1200
01:34:56,327 --> 01:34:58,887
locked within his private safe.

1201
01:34:58,887 --> 01:35:03,648
The documents which will be
published in today's papers...

1202
01:35:03,687 --> 01:35:07,848
prove that the traitor Karpov...

1203
01:35:08,348 --> 01:35:12,67
was about to steal
over 40 trillion...

1204
01:35:11,608 --> 01:35:14,368
of our precious
Russian rubles...

1205
01:35:14,408 --> 01:35:18,888
in a reckless scheme
to save his hide!

1206
01:35:18,888 --> 01:35:20,808
To add insult...

1207
01:35:20,848 --> 01:35:23,688
millions of dollars
were to be paid...

1208
01:35:23,688 --> 01:35:26,689
to this international criminal!

1209
01:35:26,729 --> 01:35:28,970
[Crowd reacting]

1210
01:35:33,369 --> 01:35:35,329
TRETIAK: And for what
was your president...

1211
01:35:35,369 --> 01:35:39,370
hoping to bankrupt
our national treasury?

1212
01:35:39,370 --> 01:35:44,490
What you see is a fairy tale
called cold fusion.

1213
01:35:44,490 --> 01:35:49,251
You pass electric current
into the machine...

1214
01:35:49,291 --> 01:35:53,371
and there is supposed
to be a chemical reaction.

1215
01:35:53,411 --> 01:35:54,932
Watch. [Beep]

1216
01:35:54,971 --> 01:35:58,451
It can't even light up
a tiny light bulb!

1217
01:35:58,491 --> 01:36:00,851
Do you dare deny this,
Mr. Karpov?

1218
01:36:00,891 --> 01:36:03,12
KARPOV: Absolutely not!

1219
01:36:03,51 --> 01:36:05,292
I proudly admit it!

1220
01:36:05,292 --> 01:36:08,291
TRETIAK:
But enough puny failure.

1221
01:36:08,332 --> 01:36:10,371
Failure's in the past!

1222
01:36:10,912 --> 01:36:14,32
Begging is behind us!

1223
01:36:14,73 --> 01:36:17,673
The balance of power
is about to shift!

1224
01:36:49,735 --> 01:36:51,695
Miracle one.

1225
01:36:56,395 --> 01:36:59,36
CROWD: Karpov! Karpov!

1226
01:36:59,75 --> 01:37:00,916
Karpov! Karpov!

1227
01:37:00,455 --> 01:37:02,616
Karpov! Karpov!

1228
01:37:02,656 --> 01:37:04,737
Karpov! Karpov!

1229
01:37:04,776 --> 01:37:06,896
Karpov! Karpov!

1230
01:37:07,437 --> 01:37:10,76
Karpov! Karpov!

1231
01:37:09,616 --> 01:37:11,416
Karpov! Karpov!

1232
01:37:11,456 --> 01:37:13,777
Karpov! Karpov!

1233
01:37:13,777 --> 01:37:15,736
Karpov! Karpov!

1234
01:37:22,738 --> 01:37:23,818
TRETIAK: Ilya! Ilya!

1235
01:37:23,857 --> 01:37:25,177
ILYA: Go! Go!

1236
01:37:25,217 --> 01:37:26,698
Go, go, go!

1237
01:37:28,179 --> 01:37:32,458
SKLAROV: I order all troops
loyal to mother Russia...

1238
01:37:32,497 --> 01:37:35,819
to seize the criminal Tretiak!

1239
01:37:41,139 --> 01:37:42,699
A thousand apologies,
Mr. President.

1240
01:37:42,738 --> 01:37:45,979
There was a miscommunication
in the chain of command.

1241
01:37:52,680 --> 01:37:54,40
[Thinking]
Miracle two.

1242
01:37:53,620 --> 01:37:56,699
NEWSWOMAN: The billionaire
industrialist and his son...

1243
01:37:56,739 --> 01:37:59,180
were taken to the infamous
Lubyanka prison...

1244
01:37:59,220 --> 01:38:03,380
where they await trial
along with General Leo Sklarov.

1245
01:38:03,380 --> 01:38:07,20
Moscow woke today to the
forgotten sensation of warmth...

1246
01:38:07,60 --> 01:38:09,221
as millions of gallons
of heating oil...

1247
01:38:09,260 --> 01:38:12,821
flowed from a storage depot
beneath Tretiak's mansion.

1248
01:38:12,821 --> 01:38:15,381
INSPECTOR: He made no threat
to contact you in the future?

1249
01:38:15,422 --> 01:38:17,182
EMMA: He never had the chance.

1250
01:38:17,221 --> 01:38:18,460
You'll tell us
if he makes contact?

1251
01:38:19,01 --> 01:38:20,121
EMMA: Yes.

1252
01:38:19,660 --> 01:38:21,102
Which he may well do.
He's a proper rogue.

1253
01:38:21,102 --> 01:38:24,221
Which he may well do.
He's a proper rogue.

1254
01:38:24,262 --> 01:38:27,702
He charms women,
this so-called Saint.

1255
01:38:28,243 --> 01:38:31,41
It seems it's his stock
in trade. No offense.

1256
01:38:31,82 --> 01:38:34,762
Well, I am offended.
All I got from this Saint...

1257
01:38:34,303 --> 01:38:36,383
was a series
of near-death experiences.

1258
01:38:36,422 --> 01:38:37,663
Count yourself lucky.

1259
01:38:37,663 --> 01:38:41,944
I have a very important
conference I must prepare for.

1260
01:38:41,983 --> 01:38:44,223
INSPECTOR: We understand.
You have a life.

1261
01:38:44,263 --> 01:38:45,903
WOMAN: We appreciate
your taking the time.

1262
01:38:45,943 --> 01:38:47,384
EMMA: No problem.

1263
01:38:54,124 --> 01:38:56,43
INSPECTOR:
She's in love with him.

1264
01:39:52,608 --> 01:39:54,09
[Giggling]

1265
01:40:03,109 --> 01:40:05,829
SIMON: I wanted to call you
and tell you everything.

1266
01:40:05,868 --> 01:40:07,29
It hasn't been safe.

1267
01:40:07,569 --> 01:40:10,89
EMMA: I couldn't stop
thinking about you.

1268
01:40:12,249 --> 01:40:17,90
SIMON:
So...have you been busy?

1269
01:40:16,630 --> 01:40:18,790
EMMA: Yeah.
I've been working real hard.

1270
01:40:19,290 --> 01:40:22,09
Thank God I have my cards back.

1271
01:40:22,09 --> 01:40:25,490
SIMON: You don't believe in
this cold fusion mumbo jumbo?

1272
01:40:25,531 --> 01:40:28,91
You know,
you're a very pretty lady.

1273
01:40:27,631 --> 01:40:29,831
EMMA: Oh, my God.

1274
01:40:29,870 --> 01:40:31,270
That was you?

1275
01:40:32,731 --> 01:40:35,90
SIMON: That's who I thought
Dr. Russell would like.

1276
01:40:35,631 --> 01:40:38,112
I thought you were
some old biddy...

1277
01:40:38,151 --> 01:40:41,391
not some gorgeous
soon-to-be-trillionaire.

1278
01:40:41,431 --> 01:40:44,232
You know you're going to be
the richest woman in the world.

1279
01:40:44,271 --> 01:40:45,352
EMMA: I am?

1280
01:40:45,391 --> 01:40:48,192
SIMON: Why do you think
I'm hanging around?

1281
01:40:54,392 --> 01:40:55,472
-Emma.
-Yeah?

1282
01:40:56,12 --> 01:40:57,693
My life is very strange.

1283
01:40:58,113 --> 01:40:59,393
I just...

1284
01:41:03,194 --> 01:41:05,273
I don't do anything normal.

1285
01:41:05,313 --> 01:41:06,793
I'm--l can't even--

1286
01:41:06,833 --> 01:41:10,153
I know. I know you.

1287
01:41:11,314 --> 01:41:13,634
